    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>OIL DEAL IN NEW ZEALAND</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Wayne Arnold</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Arnold, Wayne</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Royal Dutch/Shell Group will join with Apache of Houston to take over Fletcher Challenge Energy of New Zealand for $1.6 billion; will pay $1.03 billion for control of Fletcher's gas fields in New Zealand and Brunei; Apache will get Fletcher's oil and gas assets in Canada and Argentina for $600 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Moving to strengthen its share of Asia's market for natural gas, the Royal Dutch/Shell Group said it would join with Apache of Houston to take over Fletcher Challenge Energy of New Zealand for $1.6 billion. Shell will pay $1.03 billion for control of Fletcher's gas fields in New Zealand and Brunei. Apache will get Fletcher's oil and gas assets in Canada and Argentina for $600 million. The deal is part of a broader effort to dismantle Fletcher Challenge, one of New Zealand's largest companies.</p>
        <p>Wayne Arnold</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Moving to strengthen its share of Asia's market for natural gas, the Royal Dutch/Shell Group said it would join with Apache of Houston to take over Fletcher Challenge Energy of New Zealand for $1.6 billion. Shell will pay $1.03 billion for control of Fletcher's gas fields in New Zealand and Brunei. Apache will get Fletcher's oil and gas assets in Canada and Argentina for $600 million. The deal is part of a broader effort to dismantle Fletcher Challenge, one of New Zealand's largest companies.</p>
        <p>Wayne Arnold</p>
        <p>WORLD BUSINESS BRIEFING: ASIA</p>
